column1: you were born in 2002 in an unfortunate city with a single mom (your dad left when you were 1). growing up has been really though on the both of you. your mom working multiple jobs which were a waitress
column3: and a bartender to have enough money to get through and to pay for you boxing classes. you didn’t exactly have the perfect life at school either. you were bullied on a day to day basis
column4: you’d be beaten and have things thrown at you almost everyday because everyone knew you as the “broke girl from the broken family”. you had no friends besides one

column2: i'm not suggesting sleeping with all the guys you date
column4: that's just not my intent when i date
column5: my intent is to make sure the person i'm attracted to is mentally and emotionally mature
column6: self-aware and grounded in their own lives so when we do decide to be have sex
column7: they don't develop a co-dependent attachment to me and start giving up their social life
column9: i don't want that kind of codependent relationship.

column1: the power in taking control of your experiences is that you are actively practicing independence and that will only help you be a better communicator a more effective negotiator of your time and priorities
column2: while also making you a mindful participant as it relates to your physical safety. i think the greatest response one can have to the #metoo movement is to own the responsibility of their security and get very good at communicating their boundaries
column3: and overcoming the anxiety of saying ""no thank you"". also
column4: don't worry about guys not liking you for being too masculine
column5: or making them feel emasculated. a guy that can be made insecure by a self-directed woman is not the type of guy that will support your spiritual growth in the long run. both women and men have masculine and feminine energy. the goal is to have an equal balance of both to achieve balanced habits motivated by both
column6: then to find a man that has the same or is at least working toward it.

column1: hace  26 años fuí víctima de maltrato infantil por la negligencia de mis padres. ellos fueron drogadictos. vivíamos en un inquilinato. fui violada 2 veces por un señor
column2: que me dejaba entrar a su cuarto a ver dibujos animados; dejaba la puerta abierta siempre. hasta que un día la cerró. me destrozó mis calzoncitos y me penetró. sangré
column5: grité. nadie vino a buscarme. el señor me tapó la boca sentenciando ""no le puede decir a su papá ni a su mamá
column6: porque usted es mala y dios la castiga si le cuenta a alguien""

column2: me daba verguenza. y dios estaba enojado conmigo. fue hasta mis 11 ó 12 años
column3: que supe que no fue mi culpa. quise decirle a mi abuela (quién al enterarse de la irresponsabilidad de mis papás
column4: me sacó de ese entorno y me llevó a una vida libre de violencias)  nunca pude decírselo

column1: 26 años después quiero contarlo con esta foto. quiero abrir las piernas voluntariamente por que mi ""ser mujer"" no es menos
column2: quiero mirar y decir no tengo pena
column3: soy fuerte. mi intimidad es mucho más que lo que tapa el sombrero; mi sexualidad como dimensión humana tiene poder. y nunca más voy a callar. catalina bohórquez.

column1: 215182;instagram;2019-02-18 05:06:46;FALSE;"china’s #metoo movement will soon get its day in court | world news

column2: asia correspondent china's #metoo movement has endured a fitful existence since it emerged at the beginning of 2018
column3: facing heavy censorship online and in state media.soon
column5: it will get its day in court. on one side
column7: a television host and one of the most famous men in china. some 700 million people watch when he hosts the annual new year's eve gala on state tv.on the other
column8: a 25-year-old screenwriter called zhou xiaoxuan living in a small flat in the outskirts of beijing.four years ago
column9: ms zhou was doing work experience on one of mr zhu's shows
column10: as part of her university degree. she claims she was taken to his make-up room. image: tv host zhu jun has denied the allegations ""he said i looked like his wife and we had a similar face

column2: two days before my twentieth birthday. i woke up to birds chirping out of my window of the parents home. the parents had planned to bring arrian with to my grandmothers for the weekend
column3: so we needed to be home so i could pack her things
column4: and give her kisses good-bye. she wasn’t all smiles that morning as she had gotten her immunizations the day prior
column6: arrian again got super baby marks from the doctor as she was so advanced for her 6 month age
column7: already standing and trying to walk around her playpen. st and i would be meeting them at the grandmothers in the evening. we had planned to spend the day at valley fair (an amusement park) for my birthday gift. my younger cousin mw had flown in from washington the night before
column8: so they would also be bringing her with.

column1: توهین‌های بهروز افخمی به جامعه ال جی بی تی تمامی ندارد‼️
کسی که هیچ هنری از خود نداره مشخصا جایگاهی هم در جشنواره‌های بین‌المللی نخواهد داشت!!
رقت‌انگیزتر از این نیست که در جشنواره کن به دلیل فیلم سفارشی سازی جایگاهی ندارید و به دلیل ضعف‌ها و کمبودهاتون بگید که جشنواره کن فقط به فیلم‌های با محتوای ال جی بی تی امتیاز میده.
تا به امروز فیلم‌های انگشت‌شماری با محتوای ال جی بی تی  نامزد جشنواره‌ها شده که کن بگه من هم بلدم حمایت کنم!!
دلیل اینکه شما امتیاز و جایگاهی در جشنواره‌های بین‌المللی ندارید سفارشی سازی فیلم‌هاتون برای خوش‌آمد نظام جمهوری اسلامی هست این رو بفهمید.
۱. فیلمایی که میرن سراغ کلیشه‌های محبوب آکادمی که جایزه رو بگیرن مثل وزن کم کردن بازیگر برای ایفای نقش.
۲. فیلمایی راجع به اقلیت‌ها. اینا عموماً جایزه نمی‌برن، فقط نامزد میشن که اسکار بگه منم بلدم.
۳. فیلمای کمی که واقعاً خوبن و اشتباهی بهشون رای دادن.

نکته: این فیلمایی هم که مربوط به اقلیت‌ها هستن و به شکل تزیینی نامزد اسکار می‌شن، بهترین نمونه‌ی این دسته فیلم‌ها نیستن. مثلاً اسکار می‌ره از فیلمایی که راجع به برده‌داری ساخته شده، بی‌حاشیه‌ترینش رو انتخاب می‌کنه که حتماً توش یه سفیدپوست قهرمان داستانه. در نتیجه عملاً آب قطع‌ه.

۳. فیلمای کمی که واقعاً خوبن و اشتباهی بهشون رای دادن.

نکته: این فیلمایی هم که مربوط به اقلیت‌ها هستن و به شکل تزیینی نامزد اسکار می‌شن، بهترین نمونه‌ی این دسته فیلم‌ها نیستن. مثلاً اسکار می‌ره از فیلمایی که راجع به برده‌داری ساخته شده، بی‌حاشیه‌ترینش رو انتخاب می‌کنه که حتماً توش یه سفیدپوست قهرمان داستانه. در نتیجه عملاً آب قطع‌ه.

column1: my freaking incredible “job” ( not sure i can even call it that) comes with me wherever i go.

column2: to not have to go into work today.

column1: i don’t ever have to work for someone else’s dream.

in the next few months i am aiming to launch a (not-for-profit) project/website
column2: with a view to developing into a charity in the future
column3: for survivors of abuse and sufferers of mental health issues to speak frankly about their experiences and tell their stories. it will be called ‘power-share’ and will run on my theory that talking about our struggles weakens their hold over us
column4: creates awareness and community and inspires other people to share too.

column1: subjection to abuse and mental health issues are often very private struggles. i believe being given a platform to tell your personal account
column2: letting go of a secret that creates tension within you
column3: is freeing and allows you reclaim a sense of power and control over your life.

column2: and often a lack of support in these areas
column3: it’s uncommon to be enabled to speak freely about personal struggles and experiences. this can result in these issues never being fully faced or worked-through. i want to give you a platform to just talk about it; let it out without censoring
column4: feeling ashamed or apologising for doing so. by ‘airing’ your internal struggles i hope you can start detracting from their power over you and begin to heal.

column1: so i invite you to tell your stories and stop keeping secrets both on other people’s behalves and at your own expense. i will be leading by example and telling mine.
ways i invite you to do this: - written format
please get in touch if you are interested to share. if at any point you change your mind
column2: even once i have received your story (even if it has already been posted on the website) i will remove it immediately. no obligations
column3: this is on your terms entirely - the whole point of my project is to allow you to tell your story

column1: p.s - i will be running this project myself voluntarily due to my passion on the above issues

column1: 215352;instagram;2019-02-18 11:35:35;FALSE;"تازه‌ترین فیلم وودی آلن ممکن است تحت تأثیر اتهامات جنسی علیه این کارگردان هرگز اکران نشود

جود لا در این فیلم' نقش شخصیت ۴۵ ساله‌ای را بازی خواهد کرد که با ال فانینگ «elle fanning» (ال فانینگ در دنیای واقعی ۲۰ ساله است) رابطه جنسی دارد. با شدت گرفتن جنبش metoo# در صفحات اجتماعی قطعاً انتشار این فیلم برای آمازون یک ایده‌ی بد خواهد بود.
این جنبش #metoo هم شده شر ودردسر.
دیگه حالا نمایش عشق با فاصله سنی هم شده تابو!!!
جنبشی که قرار بود ' ابزاری برای رسیدن به عدالت و رفع خشونت جنسی بشه' حالا داره تبدیل به ابزار سانسور میشه. وروز به روز ' صف قربانیان به حق وناحقش' طولانی تر میشه.

همین جوری پیش بریم' سلام کردن به یه خانوم' ویا تعارف کردن صندلی و بازکردن در براشون هم' سوء تعبیر میشه واینکه طرف قصد داشته مخ خانوم رو بزنه پس متجاوزه و زایل کننده حقوق خانم ها' طرف هم متهم میشه به داشتن نگاه جنسیتی(سکسیستی) به زن.

column1: 215356;instagram;2019-02-18 11:41:09;FALSE;"1 year ago i quit my job
column2: because i was being mobbed by a work colleague.

column1: he was telling me every day
column2: that i am a stupid foreigner and that he doesn’t understand why anyone would hire me as a doctor in his country.

column1: i passed very tough certification exams in vienna to be able to practice as a doctor in his country.
i have been studying medicine for the past 10 years and i try to be a better doctor every day.
it wasn’t easy as a trauma surgeon at the biggest clinic in tirol.
it wasn’t easy for me as a woman and it wasn’t easy for me because german is not my mother tongue.
and here in tirol people speak a very specific dialect which wasn’t easy for me to learn.

column2: 5 years and i was getting better and better until i met this work colleague.

column1: from the beginning he wanted something more from me than just being his colleague.
after being refused by me he started torturing me psychologically.
he was telling me every day that i am a typical woman who cannot cut a bandage properly.
he was badmouthing about me to other doctors and my bosses.
i had to run away from that clinic.
i decided to go traveling to find myself back.
i didn’t want to come back to innsbruck.
i am afraid every day that i might meet him.
i am afraid to enter the clinic.
i am afraid to be a doctor
column2: because he told me every day i am useless...

column1: i have studied medicine for the past 10 years to be a great doctor and the only thing i can do now is to register myself as unemployed.
i am afraid of going out of my house.
my boyfriend is afraid i might commit a suicide.
i am afraid of being unable of doing my beloved job.
but today i managed to go to the arbeitsamt to seek for help.
and then i managed to buy myself a breakfast at a bakery close to the clinic.

column1: 215365;instagram;2019-02-18 11:44:38;FALSE;"с 13 по 17 февраля 2019 года в городе годонин (чехия) прошел международный турнир по настольному теннису. 😎
воспитанники сшор по настольному теннису «мгфсо» москомспорта завоевали 3 медали турнира. 🏅🏅🏅
золотую медаль в личном первенстве выиграл денис изумрудов. 🔥
победителями командного турнира среди юношей в составе сборной команды россии стали владислав марков и денис изумрудов. 💪🏻
среди девушек в командном первенстве серебряную медаль завоевала светлана дмитриенко. 👍🏻

column1: 215390;instagram;2019-02-18 12:18:35;FALSE;"sadly there aren’t as many women in the weights room as i’d like to see (i’m working on that!). most of the time i’m surrounded by dudes. on the whole this is not a problem
column2: the huge majority of guys in the gym are totally lovely
column4: and have supported me throughout my training

column2: i’ve encountered my fair share of gym creeps; the guy who insists on crowding my personal space
column3: makes unsolicited comments about my body
column4: stares at me whilst i do hip thrusts
column5: constantly asks if i need a spot after i’ve politely declined him
column6: and every other dude who makes me feel uncomfortable when i’m just trying to get my workout in

column1: before anyone gets angry and says ‘now men can’t do anything without upsetting women’
column2: i’m not talking about general nice chit chat
column4: or offers of help. we know the difference between leering and admiring someone’s form. this applies to all genders; absolutely anyone can experience this creepiness

column1: here’s some of my favourite tips for dealing with gym creeps:
🙅‍♀️tell the person that they’re making you feel uncomfortable. this nips the behaviour in the bud. however
column2: i appreciate this isn’t always the easiest thing to do

column1: 📣someone say something gross to you? repeat it back to them loudly so everyone can hear. that’ll shut them up
🤷‍♂️catch someone leering at you? ask them if they’re alright there
column2: do they need some help possibly using a ‘what the f*ck do you want’ tone

column1: 🎧get some headphones. these are great for tuning out everyone
🚩trust your gut instinct. if someone is throwing up red flags for you don’t ignore it
🗣tell the gym staff. you may not be the only one feeling uncomfortable
column2: and they can't take action if they don't know what's happening

column1: 💪remind yourself that you belong here. this is your gym
👫build up rapport with regular gym goers. it feels great having a few friendly faces greeting you every time you walk in

column2: when someone you don’t want approaching you does just say you let out a real stinker of a fart and they’d best clear the area. i promise they’ll never bother you again 🤣

column1: sitting with clients i often hear their desire to become normal. normal in their sleep patterns
column2: normal in the abcence of chronic pain
column4: normal in physical appearance. perhaps all of us
column6: hold a strong want and desire to feel connected to our tribe. after all these years and evolutionary changes we are still a tribal species. there is comfort or safety in the numbers at times of risk or threat. a child who is raised by the villagers does benefit from the diversity of styles and influences. to use or substitute a standard reference like normal is dangerous and a means to control the masses.

column2: especially over the last 10 to 15 years and our awakening over subjects like #metoo movement
column3: that what was considered normal as recently as 30 to 50 years ago no longer holds any water today in the acceptability column on how we treat people.

column2: on how we treated others based on the colour of their skin and it was that which determined where and what you could do has long been established as not acceptable nor right.

column1: being pleasantly plump verging on a little larger than that was considered normal and desirable and a few generations later looking skinny and gaunt were the norm.
having tattoos were considered normal for sailors not the general public and now a vast majority of our world have some ink applied.
hell at one point in time thinking that the earth was flat and sailors would fear for thier lives in sailing over the edge was normal.
there could never be a template for normal as all of us get to contribute. as all of us are unique and have different views and perspectives
column2: not one can ve considered the standard  to create a environment that holds and judges you to an ambiguous concept and labels it ""normal"" is spinning propaganda and selling something.

column2: a performance that was inspired by “the freak show” at local project art space. i earnestly wanted this work to be sickening - better than ripley’s. the result was my most personal work.

column1: a common freak show trope is the exploitation of a congenital anomaly. i’m physically able but i have post-traumatic stress disorder following two decades of sexual harassment
column3: & rape including intimate partner abuse. i’ve also been devastated by revenge from scorned suitors ranging from verbal abuse/physical threats to ostracism. for over 15 years & until recently
column4: i designed my entire life around avoiding unwanted sexual advances. i cut off my hair
column8: eschewed makeup & tried to police my speech & behavior but i’ve always presented as female & so i’ll never be safe until i reach a certain age & then i’ll be invisible.

column1: my gender is a congenital curse & because it is inborn
column2: i felt it should look naturally occurring like symmetrical markings on butterfly wings. many insects & plants protect themselves by displaying warning colors which communicate they’re poisonous or distasteful. instead of dissuading predators
column3: my body betrays me by enticing attackers. fascinated by bioluminescent phytoplankton & fungi
column4: i marked my body with invisible dark light ink.

column1: i begin fully clothed in normal light then the room is suddenly dark
column2: after a moment the black lights go on & the grotesque markings on my body burst into sight. i then discuss sexual trauma including mundane
column3: socially ordained degradation like the norm of men lying in order to seduce a female partner. lying is discouraged in courtship but this particular behavior is seen as standard protocol for heterosexual men. in reality
column4: when a man lies to a woman so he can sleep with her
column5: he is stealing access to her body by robbing her of informed consent.

column1: 215653;instagram;2019-02-18 16:39:22;FALSE;"former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel
column2: but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

column1: in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23

column3: and kushner spoke with kim darroch
column4: the british ambassador to the united states

column1: the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump
column2: who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric
column3: took office on jan. 20. it failed
column4: with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

column1: the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move
column2: egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution
column3: prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

column1: a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a ""high level"" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

column2: a member of trump's presidential transition team

column3: and kushner spoke with kim darroch

column6: who spoke on condition of anonymity.

column1: the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump
column2: who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric
column3: took office on jan. 20. it failed

column2: a member of trump's presidential transition team
column3: later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner

column2: i am saying just don't stay down...get back up
column3: remind yourself of who you are and never let anyone or anything determine your strength.

column2: i was the last in the bunch to ever join instagram. i was very hesitant to join because i assumed it revolved around vanity and showing off. i thought it was a place where people would post selfies daily
column3: pretended they lived flawless lives or pretended they were in perfect relationships but were not. and although there is a lot of people who put up fake personas out there
column4: there are also a lot of people who keep things 1000% real.

column1: i told myself that if i was going to make an instagram i would also use the platform to inspire.

in the summer of 2018 the universe decided to take me down the path of single motherhood. i started to think about how i would no longer have someone by my side at all times to help me tackle the trials & tribulations of being a parent. the amazing part of the story is that not once did i ever feel fear of the journey ahead of me nor did i feel i was incapable of what was to come. i never stopped to think about what could go wrong and instead of only what could go right.
the power we have in ourselves as women goes beyond what we can imagine.

i’ve been so inspired by our recent accomplishments like the #metoo movement and the largest women’s march in history that took place in 2017. also all the women voted into congress last year gave me the chills
column2: and seeing the way some of them are already making an impact is incredible.

column1: i want to share and celebrate the stories of women who inspire me. women who have no fear in achieving their goals and breaking the status quo or double standards. i will be featuring women with the hashtag #mujerestakethelead
you know i had to incorporate something to represent my hispanic roots
column2: hence mujeres instead of women 💃🏽 lol. but women whom i will be posting will be of all be different ages
column4: with different walks of life. women who i’ve looked up to for many years and some from my community as well. i hope you guys enjoy seeing powerful and fearless women on your feeds and i hope i can shoot a little inspiration your way.❤️ #womenempowerment #womensupportingwomen #womensupportwomen #pussypower #girlpower #women #womeninspiringwomen #women";;en;#metoo

column2: i found this sign hanging and felt it was important enough to take a photo of even though the people i was with were getting way ahead of me. the irony behind finding this when the sociopathic man who had lead us on this journey of lies and broken promises was just ahead of me walking and playing his part of ved
column3: the licensed tour guide that leads retreats and spiritual journeys to help charity organizations in india. this man has been scamming and sexual abusing women for 10 years now and has done so many women wrong that they have created a facebook group in efforts to try to congregate and get him in put in jail. with not much help from the indian embassy or police force
column4: he's still out there doing this to women. and he is using videos and photographs of mine to lure in others
column5: which pains me to see them still on youtube
column6: who won't take them down even though i've tried reporting to them what this man is doing. he has gone by many different names taj tash or tashi
column9: etc. he has stolen money from many people myself included
column10: sexually abused many women myself included
column11: lied to not only the women he's scammed but also monks and nuns who he told we would add them into our charities

column1: 215804;instagram;2019-02-18 19:29:20;FALSE;there’s something i’ve been really wanting to talk about on my instagram for a long time but have always been afraid to. after a late night talk with my husband
column2: he encouraged me to finally take the leap. i want to start posting captions on photos every so often (maybe once a week?) that talk about serious issues throughout the world. the first of which is this: sexual misconduct of any kind sucks and can have detrimental affects on the victims. i’m hesitant to open up about this since it is such a sore spot for me
column3: but i’ve experienced sexual misconduct on different levels all within about a 2 year period. first
column4: i was sexually molested by a manager at one of my old jobs working at a grocery store. this man would touch me
column6: and even customers in personal areas and call us all sorts of names. after complaining to other higher-ups in the company
column8: after a month and a half of dealing with this 5-6 days a week
column9: i quit. when i finally plucked up the courage to try to take legal action (63% of which cases like these don’t get reported at all)
column10: he got a slap on the wrist. 3 months later
column11: i woke up with a boy over my body
column13: i woke up before anything happened
column14: but think of how many women (and even men) aren’t as lucky. a year after that
column15: i unfortunately met a boy that called me all sorts of names in the book and “rated” my worth. i’ve also dealt with the “normal” cases of being cat-called and getting called names as i walked passed men in the streets. i’m not posting about this for sympathy
column16: even though my heart is beating so fast. i’m posting this because even years later
column17: i struggle so much with the trauma of what i experienced. i’m posting this because 1 in 4 women deal with sexual misconduct (in a serious sense) throughout their lives. now just imagine how many women have to deal with sexual misconduct on any level if the numbers for serious cases are as small as 1 in 4. we need to become more aware of statistics like these and educate ourselves and each other so that those we love don’t become part of a statistic. that is my prayer.;;en;;;;;;0;;laurenanciaux;☼L O☼;;0;False;112;0;0;1329;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/1a50f0de7c5b39fa1a98337038c0340c/5D03243C/t51.2885-15/e35/51510673_353901358787476_2686046077993075789_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;there’s something i’ve been really wanting to talk about on my instagram for a long time but have always been afraid to. after a late night talk with my husband

column1: 215827;instagram;2019-02-18 19:36:08;FALSE;"since 2007 (over 12+ years) mohsen milani was a religious advisor
column2: teacher and client of mine in real estate. someone who i travelled with several times and most importantly trusted! he was my trusted marriage counsellor.

column1: what i didn’t know is that
column2: for the last few years he was manipulating me as he had a sick desire. what he was doing in the background was orchestrating a divorce for his animalistic gain having no regard for a family he was about to destroy
column3: since i had trusted him. his advice at the time seemed genuine
column4: he advised me to islamically divorce my wife
column5: which i did. once he was successful in doing this
column6: he started a relationship with my wife. during this time i would speak to him and attend his mosque and travel with him. he acted like he was my best friend
column7: he would advise me to be patient and i was.

column3: i caught him in a hotel with my wife who was still legally married to me. instead of speaking the truth
column5: he started a web of lies which led to
column6: me not seeing my children for several months
column7: falsified criminal charges which were later dropped
column8: lies upon lies which had and still has defamed me in the community and public. i stood silent for 1 year! today i finally speak about the truth! not just through words but also through evidence.

column1: this video shows him chasing after me when i caught him #cheating.

i hope after my journey to be an advocate for men who are victims of imams/moulanas/skeikhs/religious marriage counsellors who do what mohsen milani did. i will also attempt to help the fathers who are victims of parental alienation on ways of how to deal with this.

column1: 215838;instagram;2019-02-18 19:49:49;FALSE;"meet our speakers: wayne county prosecutor kym l. worthy received her undergraduate degree in economics and political science from the university of michigan
column2: and her law degree from the university of notre dame school of law.  in 1984
column3: she began her legal career at the wayne county prosecutor’s office and
column4: in 1989 she became the first african-american selected by the office as a special assignment prosecutor.  she specialized in high profile murder cases
column5: including the prosecution of toni cato riggs (convicted of the murder of her husband
column6: a returning gulf war veteran) and of two detroit police officers convicted in the beating death of motorist malice green.

column3: ms. worthy came full circle in her career and returned to the wayne county prosecutor’s office
column4: this time as the wayne county prosecutor
column5: the first african american and the first female to hold the position.  she had declared her candidacy for the office for the november 2004 election.  these plans were accelerated when the incumbent resigned and she was appointed by a solid majority of the wayne county judges.

column1: she has been widely acknowledged for her courage and integrity in charging a case that could have negatively impacted her political career.  as a result of this case
column2: ms. worthy has received the following awards and honors:  2009 michigan chronicle women of excellence award; 2009 southfield-lathrup optimist club public servant of the year; 2008 detroit free press renaissance hero; 2008 radio one newsmaker of the year; 2008 channel 7 spotlight on the news newsmaker of the year; 2008 spirit of detroit award; 2008 crain’s most powerful attorneys; 2008 madd outstanding service award; 2008 cleo legacy public service award
column3: and 2008 crain’s women to watch and featured in essence magazine in february 2010.

column6: a returning gulf war veteran) and of two detroit police officers convicted in the beating death of motorist malice green.

column3: ms. wohy came full circle in her career and returned to the wayne county prosecutor’s office
column4: this time as the wayne county prosecutor
column5: the first african american and the first female to hold the position.  she had declared her candidacy for the office for the november 2004 election.  these plans were accelerated when the incumbent resigned and she was appointed by a solid majority of the wayne county judges.

column1: she has been widely acknowledged for her courage and integrity in charging a case that could have negatively impacted her political career.  as a result of this case
column2: ms. wohy has received the following awards and honors:  2009 michigan chronicle women of excellence award; 2009 southfield-lathrup optimist club public servant of the year; 2008 detroit free press renaissance hero; 2008 radio one newsmaker of the year; 2008 channel 7 spotlight on the news newsmaker of the year; 2008 spirit of detroit award; 2008 crain’s most powerful attorneys; 2008 madd outstanding service award; 2008 cleo legacy public service award
column3: and 2008 crain’s women to watch and featured in essence magazine in february 2010.

column1: 215873;instagram;2019-02-18 20:12:28;FALSE;"my journey to financial freedom had a rough start.
for most of my professional life
column2: i worked in the public + private sector.
i burned out from office politics + being in a cubicle all day.

column1: towards the end of my corporate life
column2: i got my certification at yoga teacher training.

column1: i later became a reiki master too.
it was my outlet for dealing with crazy clients
column2: passive aggressive coworkers and micromanaging bosses.

column1: it got so bad at work that i quit without a plan b lined up.

column2: i literally went into work one day and said i’m out.
i tried being a little more strategic but i just couldn’t take another day working for people that i didn’t respect.

column1: that was the start of my journey to financial independence retire early (fire). i wanted to reach a point in my finances where work became optional.
it was a wild ride to fire. but at 35
there were several times when the emergency fund came in handy.

column2: i was able to leave toxic work environments in a matter of days.

column1: running on an empty tank too?
building holistic wealth is a lifelong journey.
it's a marathon. not a sprint.
we can't always take a month long vacation but we can always make time to recharge. -

column1: 215877;instagram;2019-02-18 20:13:35;FALSE;"you are not your anxiety and/or depression.
you are not your #metoo moment(s). these may all be a part of your story.
the most amazing thing about waking up every day is you get to choose what your story will be today.
it’s not brushing anything under the rug.
the stories & events don’t just go away.
it’s choosing to feel your feelings.
it’s choosing to forgive yourself & others.
will you play the victim. or will you play the warrior?
in my 16 week mastermind “firmly you” i’m covering everything that i’ve practiced over the last 7 years to get me to where i am today.
-self-care - debunking the myths and why it’s essential.
-journaling - the mental health benefits & how it can be fun and provide you with clarity.
-what to do when you feel lonely.
-(re)discovering yourself - who you are and figuring out your wants and needs.
-toxic relationships & boundaries - this will cover romantic partners
doors close to register this friday
i have 4 spots left & then we begin our work the first week of march!
send me a message if you want in!
ps: if your heart isn’t tugging you to say hell yes! the answer is no
column2: for now. 😉 message me when your heart is ready. i’ll be here when you are with another launch of this program

215932;instagram;2019-02-18 21:02:09;FALSE;so many free events coming up @ #ifitoldyougallery @thebeaconatl with @mediumartsatlanta and lauren harris of @zucotgallery (badass women, y’all)💕 just created a huge post with the entire schedule and instagram ate it up. for now i want to definitely share that i’m hosting a listening circle this saturday evening from 7-9pm. all events are free and open to the public 🌟 all are welcome and there is no commitment beyond showing up and being an active and mindful listener. if you are moved to speak that is welcome. rooted in the quaker traditions of silence and listening as well as many native american approaches to tough conversations (as well as with my family therapist when i was 14, haha), listening is something that has been a part of my practice for 15 years. and i’m still working on it every day. it’s tough for so many of us. let’s slow down a bit, yeah? . . . . . many more events are happening (including a free soundbath the night before!!!) and i can’t wait to participate more in the atlanta community! it feels so good to make work again! 💕 #ifitoldyouatl #listeningcircle #listentoeachother #believewomen #metoo #circling column2: jag ringde en torsk och bad om hjälp och så rev vi iväg i hans skruttiga bil. det var vinter och det tunna lagret snö slingrade sig likt ormar över asfalten när han körde i rasande fart mot sin hemort i stormen. det var kolsvart runtom oss och jag hade adrenalin upp i halsen. jag vevade ner rutan och tänkte slunga ut min mobil
column3: men då slirar han till med bilen medan han rycker den ifrån mig. ”jävla dumfan! vad gör du?!” säger han roat. ”polisen kommer spåra oss!” nojar jag. ”dom kommer kunna spåra oss med den ju!”. han övertalar mig att istället linda in mobilen i aluminiumfolie. jag låter mig lugnas av att aluminiumet hindrar mobilen från att spåras. sen ger han mig tre ecstasy
column4: jag tar alla samtidigt. vi kör i fyra timmar
column5: sen stannar vi framför ett litet radhus. ”jag har fixat en som säljer allt du behöver.” säger torsken och ringer sedan ett kort samtal. sen kommer en kille på ca 30 år ut ur radhuset och sätter sig i bilen. sen divideras det om pengar och piller
column6: medan jag sitter euforisk och hög och slickar mig om läpparna efter svettdroppar. när vi kör därifrån har jag via torsken köpt opiater och kokain för 15 000kr. jag ombes ta ut samtliga tusenlappar vid en bankomat och ge till torsken. sen ger han mig allt knark och jag stoppar på mig det. när jag börjar landa från ecstasyn är vi hemma i hans lägenhet och jag står och klipper av mig håret. så att inte polisen ska känna igen mig. sen går jag in i torskens sovrum och staplar backar med ölburkar runtom mig som ett fort. så att inte polisen ska spåra mig via sändaren jag fått inopererad
column7: som jag är övertygad om. jag ber om mer aluminiumfolie att ha som tak över mitt fort. sen ligger jag i mitt fort och börjar dra linor med kokain. torsken roas av min paranoia och förvirring
column8: och utnyttjar min rädsla för polisen genom att utlova skydd och springa mina knarkärenden under rymningen i utbyte mot sällskap och sex. #metoo #prostitution #intedinhora #utanskyddsnät;;en;#metoo
